</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>When did druids pass us in melee ability?  Our skill caps are 25 higher than theirs, so our melee is (still marginally) better.<br />
<br />
I disagree on the healing aspect.  With slow (full slow) we are functional healers.  It breaks down as mobs start to mitigate slow, or be immune altogether.  Unfortunately, boosting our abilities in one also boosts the other.  Either we have no chance of healing against unslowable mobs, or if they boost that ability, then we almost never need a druid/cleric around when mobs are slowable.  I don't really see any way to fix it to leave both in a balanced state.  We are definitely not "way behind" when (full) slow is factored in.  I don't think pets should be bothered with, they are companions and like a nice extra dot, but I don't think they'll ever be (or should be) near the power of others.<br />
<br />
Definitely agree with the need for canni upgrade though, less hitting that button the better.  I don't know that passive mana regen would be in line at this point.</p>
	
	
	
