<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Chutoi</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Glor, we're never going to agree on a fix.  I wrote the following as an intro to a letter to the Dev's if we choose to use it.  Any decent letter is going to have to be long.  We just have too much to put in it, I'm afraid.  I STRONGLY recommend we don't try to suggest fixes.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
To the Sony Online Entertainment Developers . . .<br />
<br />
The shaman community has been trying for the last couple of years to come up with some form of unified commentary to express unhappiness with the state of our class.  This effort has met with failure a number of times, probably due to the sheer utility of the class.  We can solo, group and raid—so people with different play styles have different views of the basic problems.  The net result is that for the most part, we can’t agree on much of anything, other than the fact that the shaman, as a class, has issues.  <br />
<br />
With the impetus of the current spells and abilities from Gates of Discord (“GoD”), discontent seems to have increased substantially.  The general consensus is that we have reached our pinnacle of usefulness in Kunark, and, through a medium of concentrated neglect, have wound up at the bottom of the heap in just about any measure of class balance.  Mediocrity compared to the other specialized classes we can understand.  Being dead last in basically all categories is a bit much of a penalty for utility.<br />
<br />
A second difficulty the shaman are facing is that we are suffering deficiencies in so many areas, that it looks like we’re asking for the world if we suggest fixes for them!  However, in terms of balance, fixing one or two of the issues would effectively negate four or five others.  For instance, addressing damage per second (“dps”) covers nukes, damage over time spells (“DoTs”) and pets concurrently.  A fix in one of those areas might make changes in the others overpowering.  Accordingly, we decided to post a list of problems we feel need to be addressed desperately.  After all, you folks at SoE have to decide what constitutes balance in the end.<br />
<br />
Problems:</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Chutoi Dogslobber</div>
	
	
