<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Henora</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>positng this in the sticky thread instead of the other.<br />
<br />
<br />
Well, this isnt any shorter, but it is what I sent in last night.  I send one or more of these types of emails before each expansion, in the vain hope that something might be done.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Healing Power</b><br />
-No group healing ability<br />
-Smallest direct healing ability<br />
-No upgrades to our amount healed in our heal over time line, which we received in Kunark.<br />
-No MGBable/AE heal, like other priest classes and our hybrid class, beastlords.<br />
<br />
Healing needs to be re-evaluated in comparison to other healing classes, including paladins.  This review should include cast time, mana cost and amount healed.  Our heal over time spells need improvements and we need access to a group heal.  Exp group mobs hit harder in one round than we can heal.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Damage Abilities</b><br />
<i>DAMAGE OVER TIME</i><br />
-Duration of DOTs make them unattractive for use in exp groups (especially the entire disease dot line).<br />
-Agro on DOTs make them unattractive for both exp groups and raids.<br />
-Resists on shamans DOTs are high, other classes have significant -resist mods on their DOT spells.<br />
-Critical DOT aa costs twice as much as Critical Nuke AA.<br />
-Small number of DOT damage increasing focus items.<br />
<br />
Make DOTs more desirable to use in exp groups.  Bane was a step in the right direction, remove the recast time and put on a resist mod, like other classes get.  Review and reduce the amount of agro generated by shaman dots overall.  Review the cost of Critical DOT aa compared to critical nuke aa.  Compare the number of DD enhancement focus items to the number of DOT enhancement focus items.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>DIRECT DAMAGE</i><br />
-Resist rates on rains are high.<br />
-Cast time on velium strike is too long.<br />
-No nuke over 1000 damage, rangers can nuke almost as well as shamans.  All other casting classes have a higher DD spell (cleric, enchanter, mage, wizard, druid).<br />
-Highest level poison nuke is 675dmg (compare to hybrid nukes from POP expansion, RNG -700dmg, BST -675dmg, SK -660dmg)<br />
-No specialized damage increasing focus for poison nukes.<br />
<br />
Our nukes need help.  Even with major improvements to our DOT spells, we need a better nuke.  There is no reason that hybrids should be nuking on the same level us a pure caster class.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>PETS, THE FAITHFUL DOGDOG</i><br />
-Lowest DPS of all pet classes.<br />
-Low HP, our pet is one rounded, with my buffs, when attacked by mobs in LDON hard adventures.<br />
-Can't use the summoners boon LDON augment.<br />
-Pet doesn't innately dual wield.<br />
-Only one specialized pet buff, at level 50.<br />
<br />
GOD AA seems to be very focused on pet AA.  Of all the classes these new abilities are available to we will benefit the least, since our pet is the weakest.  The very high point cost for these abilities makes them very unattractive for such small benefits for shamans pets.  We have no pet buffs like other pet classes.  Even druids get a nice pet buff.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>MELEE</i><br />
-While shamans traditionally had the highest melee skill caps, now clerics are far superior meleers with bash and their summoned weapons.  Some shamans are concerned with why our melee has fallen behind.<br />
-Even with the rabid bear AA our melee is unimpressive.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Buffing</b><br />
-Stat buffs at level 65 are largely useless because of stat caps.<br />
-Our hybrid class can buff more pure HP than we can, plus more of the other relevant stats at 65, ATK and RESISTS.<br />
-Our buffs are shorter duration and higher mana cost than other priest classes.<br />
<br />
Once the masters of melee buffing, the only class that could buff ATK, shamans have seen their buffs become less and less desirable since Velious with the introduction of weapons with avatar procs, the ATK buffs from other classes and the decreasing usefulness statistic buffs.  Our hybrid class should not be buffing HP, ATK, resists, stamina and manaregen to higher numbers than we can.  There is no reason that our buffs should cost more mana and last a shorter duration than other priest classes.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Mana Regen Ability</b><br />
-Cannibalize is active mana-regen and has a large number of penalties when compared to passive mana-regen.<br />
--Permanent Spell Slot required<br />
--Cannot cast other spells when regaining mana<br />
--Cannot move while regaining mana<br />
-The current Canni upgrade is laughable and does not address any of our concerns.<br />
<br />
In the past, cannibalize and our ability to regen mana was blamed for shortcomings in other areas, such as mana cost and duration of our buffs and manacost of heals.  With the new and widespread abilities in passive manaregen for other classes, an upgrade to cannibalize 4 needs to be implemented.  We are the only class forced into a position where we have to sacrifice so much to regain mana.  Most other classes simply use a buff slot.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Debuffing</b><br />
-Slow mitigation has decreased the advantage we have over other classes that can slow.<br />
-GoD Slow upgrade is no good.  Recast times and short duration, when paired with a nerf in effectiveness of the slow makes this spell undesirable.<br />
-No upgrades to the Cripple line.<br />
<br />
<br />
In the past, it has been justified that many of the things we are lacking at (such as healing) are a result of the powerful nature of slow.  This argument is no longer valid.  Encounters are designed using slow mitigation and with full knowledge of the effects of slow.  The difference in slows between shamans and enchanters is small, beastlords are close behind with their very fast casting slow.  Other classes like bards, necromancers also have the ability to slow pretty well too.  There has been no upgrades to our cripple line in a long time.  Other classes got upgrades to their debuffs of this type (see druids).<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Shamans are plagued with the perception that we are being punished for the powerful combination of slow and torpor back in the kunark expansion.  Each and every expansion we fall farther behind other classes in healing and damage.  Our healing and damage is now more closely compared to hybrids than other priest classes.  Our two strongest points, debuffing and mana-regen have been reduced to no advantage over other classes.  It is hard to understand our role in the game.  We are no longer the best debuffer by any significant margin, nor are we a good healer or a good damage dealer.  We aren't really a pet class and our buffs are less and less sought after, we are certainly no longer the best buffing class of either melee or caster.<br />
<br />
There are many intelligent posts at The Shaman's Crucible messageboards addressing all these subjects.  Not all of them are ideal solutions or good solutions, but it is pretty easy to scan through and find some damn good ideas from some players who sincerely care about their class and the game and who have extensive experience.<br />
<br />
[removed some contact info from my original email]<br />
<br />
<br />
Thread with excellent suggestions, that already exist on this board.<br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=19063" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=19063</a><br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=19029" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=19029</a><br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=18923" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=18923</a><br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=18934" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=18934</a><br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=18448" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=18448</a><br />
<br />
and many more.</p>
	
	
	
