<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>rookz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2003<br />
	Location: california
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have been reading every thread on the topic of shaman's being out of ballance as of late, and the three largest issues that come to mind are these:<br />
<br />
Slows - we need some way of regaining dominance of slows.  I will leave it up to you all as to what that way is.<br />
<br />
Heals - The two largest complaints is our lack of group heals, and the slowness/ineffectiveness of our "fast heal".  The two most frequent "secondary" issues adressed would be an upgrade to our heal over time spells, and a better "big" heal.<br />
<br />
Cannibalism - A problem expressed quite frequently is the closing gap between our regen and others, and the still existing (if not, widening gap" of our spell 'handicaps' to make up for our "superior" mana regeneration.  Not only do our spells cost more, take longer to cast, and are less effective in order to "ballance" our dwindling advantage on mana regeneration, but we must also waste a spell slot, and a considerable amount of time in order for our regeneration to be effective.<br />
<br />
Edit: tweaked the list a bit.<br />
<br />
I have a long list of fixes to just about every one of these items, but everyone will disagree on exactly how to fix them.  In the end, the devs will make their choice anyway.  I just wanted to consolidate what looks like the 3 largest areas that need to be adressed.  Most would like a larger nuke, some major tweaks to our pet, and some sort of melee upgrade as well, but fixing everything at once would (1) never happen and (2) be arguably over powered.  Instead, I think it would be best to focus the e-mail on these three areas with a brief mention of the other areas (just to let the dev's know there are in fact other concerns).</p>
	
	
	
	
