<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sharok</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Though several of the suggestions are reasonable, we shoud really try:<br />
- to focus on a very limited number of suggestions (<= 6).<br />
- to focus on our main issues and leave away things like annoyances, minor problems or tweaks<br />
- to make suggestions possibly realistic to SoE. That means, the less SoE has to change with their current setup of spells and abilities, the better.<br />
- to not make suggestions that go against some of SoEs previous design decisions (no matter, if we agree or not). For example for some strange reason SoE cut away duration and overall efficiency of PoP spells, we shouldn't try to ask to take that back. Or obviously SoE thinks, it's a good idea to keep druids better healers than shamans, so no chance to get to equal level here. We can and should ask for a lessening of that gap though.<br />
<br />
Let me try:<br />
<br />
1) Healing<br />
<br />
Bring back Khura's mending (? the equivalent to druids big heal) and update it to 4.000 HP healed for 600 mana. Easy to do, the spell was already there.<br />
<br />
We could use a bit more update on Q, let's say 400 hp per tick for slightly higher mana costs. Again easy to do.<br />
<br />
I don't think, we are too bad on fast healing (though Tnarg's is mana intensive), group heals would be nice, but aren't a necessity, so i wouldn't ask for it.<br />
<br />
2) DPS<br />
<br />
Lower overall aggro on DoTs, lower the recast rate of fast casting DoTs (Bane line). A complete overhaul, how DoTs work (aggro, counters, duration - efficiency) would be in order, but i don't see that coming.<br />
<br />
Give us a faster casting DD (6 secs?) with a small resist modifier and damage in the 1.3 - 1.5 K range.<br />
<br />
When SoE wants to push shaman more towards 'pet class', give us a noticable more powerful high level pet.<br />
<br />
3) Buffs<br />
<br />
The relative lessening of our buffs importance is an issue caused by game mechanics (stat caps, mudflation, general EQ stat system). Honestly i don't see many substantial updates here. Maybe some AA, that improves duration of ALL avatar spells for 10, 20 and 50 percent? Would at least lessen the pain of constant avatar rebuffing a bit. But i would even leave that away to focus on the really burning issues.<br />
<br />
4) Slows<br />
<br />
Same as buffs here, problems are caused by game design and mechanics. I would settle for a new slow with noticable higher mana costs, a significant MR modifier and same cast time as Turgur's.<br />
<br />
This would basically split slows in two lines:<br />
The 'everyday' slow Turgur's for normal xp grind.<br />
The expert slow (shaman only) for challenging content and raid targets.<br />
<br />
5) Canni<br />
<br />
A true Canni update, that allows shaman to canni larger chunks of HPs once, for example 300 HP for 160 mana with a longer recast time than Canni IV (between 1.6 and 1.8 times as long). Overall two goals should be achieved with the update: the shaman does have to spend less time on canning and the overall mana/time regeneration rate should be increased slightly.<br />
<br />
Please feel free to tweak the numbers, as i really suck at number crunching.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />lvl 65 barbarian shaman<br />
{Tuatha de Danann}<br />
on the Tribunal<br />
-------------------------<br />
<font size="1">Chronos reincarnated as a bear</font></div>
	
	
