<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Splitzer</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2003<br />
	Location: Bristlebane, CoL
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>It seems to me that a shaman's strength and focus is in indirect damage/healing through buffs/debuffs and longer duration heals/DoTs.  Instead of copying the abilities and strengths of other classes, boost ours to a point where they're viable again.<br />
<br />
One thing that's being left out of most discussions is our buffs/debuffs.  Time and time again, we're referred to as the kings of buffs.  Nowdays this is simply because we have more buffs than anyone else since a very small percentage of them are useful at all anymore.  Melees would once quite literally cheer whenever a shaman joined the group.  Put us back up to that level with buffs to directly affect avoidance, dodge, weapon skills, mitigation, strikethrough, endurance, accuracy, etc. With disciplines being treated as spells now, I KNOW this sort of thing is possible.  Make these buffs long lasting like our stat buffs and have a very noticable effect on the buffed atribute (not one that requires logs and a parser to see). Give us a short term Avatar style buff that has a huge effect on offensive melee abilities, preferably as a group buff that can be MGB'd.<br />
<br />
Cripple just doesn't cut it as a melee debuff anymore.  Take some of the proposed buffs from above and use them as debuffs.  Make these debuffs have a noticable effect like the buffs.<br />
<br />
Instead of increasing our burst heals, our healing power could be greatly increased by giving us a massive duration heal.  Something along the lines of 650+ per tic for 4-6 tics.  We wouldn't be healing for boss mobs like a druid or a cleric can, but we'd make the cut for an xp group.  A group version of quies as it stands now (maybe toss in a pois/dis/curse cure as a nod to our supposedly superior curing abilities) as an aa that we could MGB is also highly desirable.<br />
<br />
A larger selection of fast-acting DoTs with the resist mods given to other classes and no extended recast time would make up for current lack of DPS.  Bring the agro from DoTs back in line with the agro from nukes and we'll actually use them.<br />
<br />
A larger spell-based canni and an aa to reduce the re-use timer on cannibalization would cut a lot of the tedium and detriments from our activated mana regen that is no longer superior to what other classes are capable of.<br />
<br />
As an upgrade to our level 51 slow, give us a fast-casting 70-75% slow with a resist mod equal to Malos.  Leave off any kind of extended recast and you've' got an upgrade that everyone would use.  Add in a n extra debuff or two just for icing.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=08c1db0e5161aa1353609228d465e0a8&amp;postid=214843">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=08c1db0e5161aa1353609228d465e0a8&amp;do=getip&postid=214843">Logged</a></div>
	
	<!-- / message -->
		
	</td>
