2. Improve Quiescence - The upgrade to torpor only removed the snare/root effect.  There was no increase to healing power.<br />
<br />
3. Improve Spear of Torment - increase damage received from this spell.  This was merely a reduced cast time/mana from the 54 version.  Change to around 840 or so.<br />
<br />
4. Improve Velium Strike - This nuke should be increased to 1020 or so damage and maybe a second off cast time.<br />
<br />
5. Improve rain spells - increase the damage from our top two rain spells to match how effective that level of spell should be.<br />
<br />
6. Increase pets - increase relative pet power to be a pet or two behind mages/necros.<br />
<br />
7. Overall detrimental spells - add resist modifiers as the other dot classes have.<br />
<br />
8. Melee output - Reduce cleric bash ability and/or give us some melee benefit(modifier, higher skill, etc.)<br />
<br />
Note: Not all suggestions should be taken as a chunk, this might cause balance issues.   The most appropriate ones would be reduction of paladin heals and upgrading of our spells.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>You have some solid ideas here, but dont try to strengthen our position by calling for a nerf on another; not only does it breed animosity between the classes, but it makes us seem more class envious than actually concered that we have short comings.<br />
I have said it before and will say it again, give paladins all the healing they want, if some vocal minorty of them feels that they need a 1 sec cast time CH with a 1 min refresh so they can main heal in BoT and they can convince the devs to give it to them, then /cheers. 95% of the Paladins you talk to are fine with their healing capability. I am as well. So should you be.</p>
	
	
	
