<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Fascaser</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Not to over simplify things but there seems to a trend across posts on possible spell updates.  Is it possible as a class that we are close to consensus for an expansion?<br />
<br />
Instead of creating wish lists, we are outlining the top issues for the post 65 stage of the game.   A fair problems list along with companion reasonable corrections surely should get the Dev’s attention's who are struggling to create balanced spells while placating Shaman’s frustrations with past expansion spell’s post Kunark.<br />
<br />
<br />
At least to me it is something like a choice of following for GoD <br />
<br />
1). Healing<br />
Common suggestions: <br />
Either - Group HoT for the class - something like Group Quiescence (with MGB option)<br />
Or – Increased Direct Heal<br />
<br />
2). Damage Output – one of the following<br />
DD - Common suggestion: Upgrade to DD - something like Poison DD with 1.X k plus damage<br />
Dot - Common Suggestion: Upgraded DoT - something like fast damage DoT for 750-1k per tick, 2-3 tick duration, low resist, high agro usable for group encounters<br />
Melee - Common Suggestion: Major Upgrade to AA Rabid bear or Bear form spell<br />
<br />
3). Debuffs<br />
Resist Debuffs - Common Suggestion: Upgrade Cripple line<br />
<br />
4). Mana Regen<br />
Cannibalize line - Common Suggestion: Upgrade to Can 4 based on higher HP pool's post PoP Expansion<br />
<br />
5). Buffing<br />
Increase duration and capabilities – Common Suggestion: Upgrade duration and/or combinations for group stackable buffs</p>
	
	
	
