	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Do you mean, malosinia? Malos is un-resistable (which is what I meant by "quite a resist mod").<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Nah, I'm not suggesting to make it unresistable like Malos, just to give it a better chance to land as though we has cast malos already, not combine the two into one spell.  Malos would still be needed as a resist debuff.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Lets get some realistic ideas here...upgrade Q to 350/tick<hr size="1" /></blockquote>I'll admit to picking out one point of your post and nitpicking, but adding 50hps to quies is NOT an upgrade worth asking for.  To keep us in line with the heal upgrades clerics and druids are getting in GoD (given the same ratio torpor had to druid and cleric heals at the time) it would need to do 575/tick for four ticks.  That's a 2300 point heal.  Yeah, that's almost twice the healing power of torpor.  For comparison though, look at Ethereal Light (1600hp Luclin era cleric heal) vs Holy Light (3050hps proposed GoD cleric heal).  Clerics have almost doubled their healing power.  Same goes for druids.  The fact that it seems over the top and unrealistic just goes to show how far we've slipped in respect to the other priests.  As an added bonus, the other priests' basic heals have become on average 1.5s faster casting.  Ours are still slow.<br />
<br />
On the other hand, I like your idea of adding ATK to Focus.  Perhaps toss a bit more hps on there (nothing major) and throw in a (small) boost to mitigation with a Bulwark of Vie style effect.  Again, nothing big, maybe just 3-5%.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
