<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Caanus Grey</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Dying differently everyday<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Most every class that has a "defining ability" has many ways in which they can approach it.  Clerics can C-heal, quick heal, sacrafice group health then group heal, or heal over time.  Nuke classes get to nuke at least 3 different resists.  Melee classes can go ranged, 1 handers, 2 handers.  Hybrids can melee, nuke, or even assist with healing.  Enchanters can mezz, stun, charm or nuke (don't think they can root).<br />
<br />
<br />
   We can do quite a few of the above listed things in ONE WAY.  Lately that isn't a very unique statement though, EVERYONE can do most of those abilities in their own fashion anymore.  Let's face it, we are down to finally being no more the second-rate of each ability, we are now specialized as....<br />
<br />
  THE MAIN SLOWER!   So, since slowing is most definately our schtick, it is about time we had more than 1 way to do it.  We have Turgur, and we have Grummus.  Grummus is ONLY used when Turgur CANNOT be used, so this is not another option, this is another path.   Where are the other slowing methods that we can choose from?  Maybe a hiccup spell that is a "stun over time" giving the mob a guaranteed 4.5 second stun at the start of each tick (if the spell wasn't resisted upon casting).  This would in essence be a 75% slow, but the catch is it wouldn't be a mitigatable slow.  Mobs tagged immune to stun would of course be quite immune to this as well.  If it were desired they could go with lower duration stuns like 3 seconds (50% slow) and if mitigation is widespread enough we would still use it.<br />
<br />
<br />
  Or they could be less creative and just add Cripple to slow, add a DoT to slow, have slows that increase fizzle rates or any range of other small added effect WHILE LEAVING THE SLOW COMPONENT AT NO LESS THAN 70%.   Remember, as long as we have the option of a better percent slow, everybody in the group/raid will want that one, including the shaman (unless added effect is VERY considerable).<br />
<br />
  I can only see 3 reasons that we aren't getting upgrades.<br />
1) They are afraid to raise the percentage of any slow past 75% because it would trivialize all prior encounters.<br />
2) They are afraid to improve our healing because the better we heal the better we recover mana (even though we have little to spend that mana on anymore)<br />
3) They are simply out of ideas on what else we CAN buff and finally realize that we don't need 5 more to each stat.<br />
<br />
<br />
  So all in all, seems like it is time for some new ideas, or some EXTENSIVE testing on the test server to see if improving our healing ability or slow ability really would unbalance things.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
EDIT:  I even thought of a semi-creative way to improve our buffing and once more make us the KING OF BUFFERS!  Why not give us at level 65 buffs which raise the STAT CAPS instead of the stats themselves?  Since the major complaint about the stat buffs is the fact people are OVER their max allowed, why not let us explore just how far over they really are?  That would make the stat buffs a bit more worthwhile to me personally.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83158>Caanus Grey</a><BR/><br />
Barbarian Prophet</div>
	
